article.headline: Talladega 65, Alabama A&amp,M 60
article.story:
NORMAL, Ala. -- Jerel Davis scored 19 points and blocked 11 shots to lead Talladega past Alabama A&M 65-60 on Saturday night.

Davis went 8 of 9 from the field, including two baskets during Talladega's 7-2 spurt in the final two minutes.

Talladega (6-3) led 58-56 with 1:56 remaining before Davis hit a jumper to tie the game.

Drew Washington, who finished with 10 points, then hit a 3-pointer with 1:21 remaining to put Talladega ahead for the first time since 6:32 left in the first half.

Alabama A&M (0-2) led 32-23 in the first half before shooting 9-for-34 from the field. The Bulldogs committed 10 of their 15 turnovers in the second half.

Tarium Taylor added 14 points and 10 rebounds for Talladega.

Cornelius Hester and Jonathan Inman each scored 13 points for Alabama A&M.
